                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/79: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-24T10:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1920—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. New Bolivian Government has requested Brazilian Government to grant it
                    recognition. Alencar<note n="3" xml:id="d383fn3">Augusto Cochrane de Alencar,
                        Brazilian Ambassador at Washington.</note> has been instructed to inquire
                        <pb facs="0476" n="378" xml:id="pg_378"/> whether American Government
                    intends to recognize. Embassy will appreciate an intimation as to Department’s
                    intention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
